          <td valign="top">

<span class="txth1">Vim Blog : An updated plugin to allow you to post from VIM to Wordpress</span> 

<br>
<br>

<!-- karma table -->
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="1" bordercolor="#000066">
<tr>
  <td class="lightbg"><b>&nbsp;script karma&nbsp;</b></td>
  <td>
    Rating <b>13/4</b>,
    Downloaded by 110  </td>
  <td class="lightbg">
  <b>&nbsp;Comments, bugs, improvements&nbsp;</b>
  </td>
  <td>
    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Script:3475">Vim wiki</a>
  </td>  
</tr>
</table>
<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=27480">Josh Kenzer</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td> took the popular vimpress plugin and added the ability to upload images and set a post status type (draft or published). <br><br><br>Commands :<br>&quot;:BlogList [count]&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Lists the last x articles in the blog - if left blank 10 are returned<br>&quot;:BlogNew&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Opens page to write new article<br>&quot;:BlogOpen &lt;id&gt;&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Opens the article &lt;id&gt; for edition<br>&quot;:BlogDel &lt;id&gt;&quot; <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Del the article &lt;id&gt;<br>&quot;:BlogSend&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Saves the article to the blog if the Post Status is draft. Posts the<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;article to the blog if the Post Status is publish<br>&quot;:BlogUp &lt;image name&gt;&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Uploads an image to the blog and inserts the image url. It will use the<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;img_template var to fill in a whole img tag if wanted. Use %s where you'd<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;like the actual url to be.<br>&quot;&lt;leader&gt;c&quot;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Must be in insert mode.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Displays an auto-complete list of available blog categories. Currently<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;only supported after :BlogNew<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;You can remap this on line 69</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td>Place in your vim/plugin/ directory.<br><br>Edit the settings starting on line 82<br><br>This plugin does require that python be compiled into vim</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

